[recv] {"method":"item/completed","params":{"item":{"type":"agentMessage","id":"msg_04d786f48f7885c80169c54b8559f881919c4c19db043821b6","text":"Implemented a minimal RP2040 breakout in [index.circuit.tsx](/workspace/index.circuit.tsx) using only imported JLCPCB parts for the RP2040, USB-C receptacle, flash, crystal, and LDO from [imports/RP2040.tsx](/workspace/imports/RP2040.tsx), [imports/TYPE_C_16PIN_2MD_073_.tsx](/workspace/imports/TYPE_C_16PIN_2MD_073_.tsx), [imports/W25Q16JVUXIQ.tsx](/workspace/imports/W25Q16JVUXIQ.tsx), [imports/X322512MSB4SI.tsx](/workspace/imports/X322512MSB4SI.tsx), and [imports/XC6206P332MR.tsx](/workspace/imports/XC6206P332MR.tsx). The board includes USB power/data, 3.3 V regulation, QSPI flash, 12 MHz crystal, RUN pull-up, a GPIO25 LED, and two side headers exposing GPIO plus SWD.\n\nValidation:\n- `npm run typecheck`: passed\n- `tsci check netlist index.circuit.tsx`: passed with 0 errors / 0 warnings\n- `tsci check placement index.circuit.tsx`: passed after rotating the headers vertically\n\nLimitation: `tsci build index.circuit.tsx` and `tsci snapshot index.circuit.tsx --pcb-only` did not return within 30 seconds in this environment, so I could not confirm the final routed build artifact.","phase":"final_answer","memoryCitation":null},"threadId":"019d2aa6-3aa2-7320-8af1-bfcc8c7c1636","turnId":"019d2aa6-3aa7-7441-b02f-3173c04f8679"}}
